title: Logo Design for Law Firm
description:
The target for the campaign are adults who have been injured with a focus on Men & Women ages 25-54
The client wants the logo to appeal to both English and Spanish persona. So they want a logo that would stand out and appeal to an unacculturated Spanish persona, but the client does NOT want it to be over the top Spanish. No Mariachi, No Lucha Libre etc.
other_notes:
General background
Logo is to be used for “Valero & Valero” a personal injury law firm specializing in auto accidents that is owned by a father and son.
Target audience:
The target for the campaign are adults who have been injured with a focus on Men & Women ages 25-54
The client wants the logo to appeal to both English and Spanish persona. So they want a logo that would stand out and appeal to an unacculturated Spanish persona, but the client does NOT want it to be over the top Spanish. No Mariache, No Lucha Lebra etc.
General direction on the logo
The client wants a logo that instills trust, provides creditability, is clean and easy to read overall. They like a professional look, but they don’t want it to be to corporate or buttoned up. They are not opposed to more classic legal like times new roman, but tend to lean towards a more modern look that could have less structured fonts and shapes. IE use a simple icon, strong but simple font, simple color palate.
They are open to having elements within the logo that are intuitive to legal service or Personal Injury Law, but down want it to be cartoony.
The client prefers to stay away from Cliché legal icons like a gavel, scales of justice etc.
Examples of the type of logos they like are attached
These are meant as inspiration, not content to copy from.
Colors
They are open to different options but Nothing crazy or loud. They would lean toward simplicity using 1-2 colors. Just a simple black font would likely be fine.
They like Blue as a color that instill confidence. They lean towards colors like Blue, Black and grey but open to seeing different options.
Random thoughts
In reviewing the Boxed Water site they loved the logo for how clean it is. We sort of explored the idea of using a similar font, black logo that had “Valero” Directly over “Valero” with an “&” to the right taking up the verticle area of both names and be extremely similar to the boxed water logo. We would definitely like to see some options like that.

title: Design a creative and serene logo for our retail brand
description: We are a retail company that sells a variety of products from kids toys to home decor. Because our market is wide and our customers vary - we want our logo to be simple and modern, with a recognizable icon/graphic piece along with the name.
other_notes: Our brand wants to have the feeling of being inviting, calm and serene, and welcoming. We would like the colors to represent that feel. We also are open to an abstract interpretation to our name as well as literal - we want to see some creativity!
